-- Mumbai, New Delhi on High Alert For 26/11 Terror Anniversary, Times Says
-- B y   M a d e l e n e   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-11-19T01:37:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/mumbai-new-delhi-on-high-alert-for-26-11-terror-anniversary-times-says.html
India’s Union home ministry has put
Mumbai and New Delhi on high alert following “specific inputs”
from a western intelligence agency of possible terror attacks
during the 26/11 anniversary, the Times of India reported,
citing an official it didn’t identify.  In advisories to the Maharashtra and New Delhi police, the
Union home ministry has asked them to increase vigilance in
crowded public places as well as around important public
buildings and sensitive installations, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Madelene Pearson in Mumbai at 
 mpearson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
